The generated deserialization code for `NspAccessRuleProperties.Subscriptions` (typed as `IReadOnlyList`) does not correctly deserialize `SubResource` items from the JSON array. A custom deserialization hook via `[CodeGenSerialization]` is required as a workaround.

## Affected Model

- `NspAccessRuleProperties` (`sdk/storage/Azure.ResourceManager.Storage/src/Generated/Models/NspAccessRuleProperties.cs`)

## Current Workaround

A `[CodeGenSerialization]` attribute with a custom deserialization hook is used in customization code:

```csharp
[CodeGenSerialization(nameof(Subscriptions), DeserializationValueHook = nameof(DeserializeSubscriptionsList))]
public partial class NspAccessRuleProperties
{
    internal static void DeserializeSubscriptionsList(JsonProperty property, ref IReadOnlyList subscriptions)
    {
        // Manual deserialization using ModelReaderWriter.Read()
    }
}
```

## Expected Behavior

The generator should correctly deserialize `SubResource` collection properties without requiring custom hooks.

